-- Mexico Stocks: Urbi Desarrollos, Cemex, Homex, Penoles
-- B y   C a r l o s   M a n u e l   R o d r i g u e z
-- 2012-03-21T21:42:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-21/mexico-stocks-urbi-cemex-homex-industrias-penoles-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading.  The IPC index rose 1 percent to 38,434.51.  Construction-related companies led Mexican stocks higher on
speculation recent declines were overdone, said  Carlos Gonzalez ,
an analyst with Monex Casa de Bolsa in Mexico City. The Habita
index of six homebuilders trades at 8.47 times trailing 12-month
earnings, down from a peak this year of 9.46 on Feb. 13.  Urbi Desarrollos Urbanos SAB (URBI*)  , Mexico’s third-
largest homebuilder, rose 4.1 percent to 14.85 pesos.
 Desarrolladora Homex SAB (HOMEX*)  , the nation’s largest
homebuilder, climbed 3.1 percent to 40.96 pesos.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO) 
, the largest cement maker in the Americas, jumped
4 percent to 10.33 pesos.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES*)  (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, rose 3.4 percent to 619.77 pesos as silver
futures for May delivery gained as much as 1.8 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carlos M. Rodriguez in Mexico City at 
 carlosmr@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
